    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Bacopa monnieri are used to enhance cognitive function and memory, and they are typically standardized to contain 20-50% bacosides. Bacopa capsules are the most common preparation, providing a controlled release of bacosides into the bloodstream. Bacopa tincture is another preparation, often standardized to contain 10-20% bacosides, and is used for its bioavailability and ease of administration. Bacopa tea is a less concentrated preparation, typically made by infusing dried Bacopa leaves in hot water, and contains lower levels of bacosides compared to other preparations. Bacopa extract and infusion are also used, with the former often being a concentrated extract of bacosides and the latter being a less concentrated preparation similar to tea.",
