    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Bacopa monnieri improperly are exhibits sedation due to its GABAergic and dopaminergic effects, experiences seizures in rare cases due to its potential interaction with certain medications that lower the seizure threshold, experiencing nausea and stomach upset due to its gastroirritant properties and potential interaction with certain medications that affect gut motility, and experiencing gastrointestinal distress such as diarrhea and abdominal pain in some individuals. Bacopa monnieri's mechanism of action involves increasing the synthesis of brain-derived neurotrophic factor (BDNF), which may contribute to its potential side effects. The improper use of Bacopa monnieri may also lead to its interaction with other medications, such as blood thinners and diabetes medications, which may exacerbate its side effects. The individual's health status, including any pre-existing medical conditions, and the dosage and duration of Bacopa monnieri use may also influence the likelihood and severity of its side effects. Additionally, Bacopa monnieri's potential interaction with other herbs and supplements may also contribute to its side effects."
